Polish Stocks: Bank Handlowy, Pekao, Polskie Gornictwo Shares

-- B y   P a w e l   K o z l o w s k i
-- 
2011-12-02T17:17:36Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-02/polish-stocks-kghm-lotos-pkn-orlen-polskie-gornictwo-shares.html
Poland’s  WIG20 Index (WIG20)  declined for a
second day, losing 7.13, or 0.3 percent, to 2,257.90 at the
close in Warsaw. The measure gained 4.4 percent this week.  The following are among the most active stocks on the
 Warsaw Stock Exchange  today. Stock symbols follow company names.  Bank Pekao SA (PEO)  , majority-owned by UniCredit SpA,
increased 1.5 percent to 145 zloty and  Bank Handlowy SA (BHW)  , a unit of Citigroup Inc., added 1.5 percent to 72.5 zloty.  Banks gained across  Europe  as U.S. unemployment rate fell
while Germany and  France  pushed for greater fiscal union in the
euro area.  Polskie Gornictwo Naftowe i Gazownictwo SA (PGN)  , the
largest Polish natural-gas distributor, advanced 1.3 percent to
4.02 zloty, extending this week’s increase to 2.6 percent. The
company and power utility Tauron Polska Energia SA may pick a
builder for their jointly owned gas-fired power plant in
December, the Rzeczpospolita newspaper reported on its Rp.pl
website, citing PGNiG’s Chief Financial Officer Slawomir Hinc.  Construction may start in the first quarter, the newspaper
said, citing Tomasz Kras, PGNiG’s head of strategy.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Pawel Kozlowski in Warsaw 
